<Base title="Q4 2025 Update — Adam Penn" description="Quarterly founder update: Q4 2025. Wrapping up the year — what worked, what didn't, and what's next.">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="page-header">
      <a href="/updates" class="update-back">All Updates</a>
      <h1>Quarterly Founder Update — Q4 2025</h1>
      <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-light);">December 2025</p>
    </div>

    <section class="section update-content">

      <h2>Wins</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Launched the Bidwell Capital Fund STR fund structure. First investors committed, and the pipeline is growing.</li>
        <li>Penn Properties portfolio hit 35+ managed units. Operations are getting tighter as we standardize across properties.</li>
        <li>The Wealth Independence Podcast crossed 60 episodes. Starting to see real traction in the tech professional audience.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Lessons</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Growth without systems creates chaos. I spent a big chunk of Q4 building internal processes I should have built earlier.</li>
        <li>Investor communication is a product, not a chore. The better I communicate, the stronger the relationships — and the easier future fundraising becomes.</li>
        <li>Taking a week completely offline in November was one of the best business decisions I made all year. Came back with better clarity on priorities.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I'm Focusing On Next</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Q1 fundraising push for Bidwell Capital Fund.</li>
        <li>Implementing new property management software across the Penn Properties portfolio.</li>
        <li>Planning the 2026 podcast season with a tighter editorial calendar.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I'm Reading & Thinking About</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Finished <em>Same as Ever</em> by Morgan Housel. The chapter on risk and the stories we tell ourselves stuck with me.</li>
        <li>Thinking about what "enough" looks like — not as a ceiling, but as a compass for decision-making.</li>
      </ul>

    </section>

  </div>
